text: In the last 5 years EU membership has not increased net employment in Britain. But we have created jobs for EU citizens - around 1 million

users.name: David Davis

text: (3/3) The impact of EU membership has been deleterious to the poorest workers. Their job prospects and their wages have both been reduced
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: (2/3) There is significant evidence from the Bank of England among others that migration pressure has depressed the lowest wages
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

users.name: David Davis

users.name: David Davis

users.name: David Davis

users.name: David Davis

text: (1/5) Since 2010 about 2.5 million jobs have been created in the UK

users.name: David Davis

text: The share of our exports going to the EU has dropped from over 60% to about 42%; this is set to fall further in the future
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: (3/3) But now after 40 years in Europe we are no better off than when we started https://t.co/EvQ0Jm5Esq

users.name: David Davis

text: (2/3) In 1973 we were a tottering industrial economy, and the EEC was a modern, go ahead, trade bloc
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: The Treasury forecast is not an economic forecast. It is a political forecast, with a political purpose
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: (2/2) The Treasury cannot accurately forecast 6 months. Why should we believe they can forecast 15 years?
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: (1/2) Last year the Treasury found £27bn down the back of the sofa, only to be strapped for cash by Spring
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: The Treasury and the IMF claim #Brexit will cost economic growth but neither have a good track record on forecasting
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: (3/3) Time after time the elite have got it wrong, and the ordinary people, whose wisdom was derided, have paid the price
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: (2/3)The Gold Standard. Appeasement. The ERM. On the continent, the Euro. Globally, the 2008 Crash. And we haven’t heard from Chilcot yet...
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: (1/3) The British and international establishment do not have a great track record when it comes to the great questions of their era
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: Today I want to unpick some of Remain’s arguments and expose them to factual analysis
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: The entire Remain case has been, if I may mimic @BorisJohnson, one big ‘argumentum ad verecundiam’
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: Remain have bombarded us with scare tactics, myths of the miracles the EU brings and the disasters that will allegedly rain down if we leave
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: To watch my full contribution to today’s debate on the #SyriaVote see: https://t.co/8oYCbqAIvf
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: If the UK is to stand alongside France we should do something with a chance of success, and not mere symbolism. #SyriaVote
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: (5/5) These actions will not destroy IS, but it will do a great deal more harm than a largely symbolic bombing mission in #Syria
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: (4/5) Secondly, Saudi Arabia and Gulf states should stop the 10’s of millions of dollars of funding that come yearly from them
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: (3/5) Two things can be done. NATO can insist Turkey shuts its border with #Syria. Cutting the $1billion funding from IS oil sales
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: (2/5) This is not a choice between action and inaction. It is a choice between inaction and distraction
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: (1/5) The arguments of those saying 'doing something in #Syria is better than nothing' are false. Nobody is arguing for doing nothing
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: (2/2) The limit is number of targets. The Americans get few from the rebels. We have to create a real army on the ground. #SyriaVote
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: (1/2) It is debatable whether British airstrikes would have any effect. At the moment the US fly 7 sorties a day–against 140 Russian sorties
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: We are proposing to join a strategy having the opposite effect to that intended. IS recruitment now doubled from 15,000 to 30,000 personnel
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: The US air campaign aims to degrade IS. The reality is that IS are now bigger than at the beginning of the campaign
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis

text: Everyone wants to see the end of IS. Today’s #SyriaVote is about the practical method of going about it
users.description: Conservative Member of Parliament for Haltemprice and Howden.
users.name: David Davis
